      Starts an active devices discovery.
      Note: this method should run on a background thread.

      This method will block during initialization of scanning dependencies and if this initialization fails a RuntimeException will be thrown,
      after the initialization phase the method will return an keep scanning in the background,
      any errors in this phase will be sent to DiscoveryEventListener.onDiscoveryError(CommunicationInterface, ErrorCode)

      Note: Cameras can be reported as found even if they aren't connectable, depending on the implementation (entries could be cached in system services).
      Similarly camera lost events might be delayed, depending on the implementation (some implementations are only refreshed once per 5 minutes).
      One should connect to the camera if faster feedback is required.

      • scan

        public void scan(@NotNull
                 @NotNull DiscoveryEventListener listener,
                 @NotNull
                 CommunicationInterface... communicationInterfaces)
        Starts an active devices discovery.
        Note: this method should run on a background thread.

        This method will block during initialization of scanning dependencies and if this initialization fails a RuntimeException will be thrown,
        after the initialization phase the method will return an keep scanning in the background,
        any errors in this phase will be sent to DiscoveryEventListener.onDiscoveryError(CommunicationInterface, ErrorCode)

        Note: Cameras can be reported as found even if they aren't connectable, depending on the implementation (entries could be cached in system services).
        Similarly camera lost events might be delayed, depending on the implementation (some implementations are only refreshed once per 5 minutes).
        One should connect to the camera if faster feedback is required.
        Parameters:
        listener - a listener for different discovery events or errors,
        communicationInterfaces - the interfaces that should be used in the scan

      • stop

        public void stop(@NotNull
                 CommunicationInterface... communicationInterfaces)
        Stops all active scans on the specified interfaces. Does nothing if no scan is active on a specified interface.
        This method is asynchronous and can be run on any thread.
        A client can call scan(DiscoveryEventListener, CommunicationInterface...) directly after calling "stop()".
        Parameters:
        communicationInterfaces - the interfaces for which scan should be stopped

      • stop

        public void stop()
        Stops all active scans. Does nothing if no scan is active.
        This method is asynchronous and can be run on any thread.
        A client can call scan(DiscoveryEventListener, CommunicationInterface...) directly after calling "stop()".
